  "local_port": 49190,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I restore misc files from phone?",
  "response": "Restoring miscellaneous files from your phone can vary depending on the type of phone you have (Android or iOS) and the backup options you use. Here are some steps for both Android and iOS devices:\n\n### Android:\n\n#### Google Drive Backup:\n1. **Ensure Backup:** Verify that your files are backed up to Google Drive. You can check this by going to \"Settings\" > \"Google\" > \"Backup.\"\n2. **Restore Backup:**\n   - **Reinstalling Apps:** If you are restoring files related to specific apps, reinstalling the apps may prompt them to pull data from Google Drive.\n   - **Download Files:** Navigate to the Google Drive app and download the files you need.\n\n#### Local Backup (SD Card/PC):\n1. **Connect to PC:** Connect your phone to your computer using a USB cable.\n2. **Access Storage:** Open the phone\u2019s storage on your computer. Look for the \u201cMiscellaneous\u201d or \u201cMisc\u201d folder.\n3. **Copy Files:** Copy the files you want to restore back to the phone\u2019s internal storage or SD card.\n\n#### Third-Party Backup Apps:\n1. **Open App:** Open the third-party backup app (e.g., Titanium Backup, Helium Backup).\n2. **Restore:** Use the app\u2019s restore function to get your miscellaneous files back.\n\n### iOS:\n\n#### iCloud Backup:\n1. **Check Backup:** Ensure that your files are backed up to iCloud. You can check this by going to \"Settings\" > \"[Your Name]\" > \"iCloud\" > \"Manage Storage\" > \"Backups.\"\n2. **Restore Backup:** You can restore your phone from an iCloud backup during the initial setup if you are restoring everything or browse files in the iCloud Drive app and download specific files.\n\n#### iTunes (or Finder on macOS):\n1. **Open iTunes/Finder:** Connect your device to your computer and open iTunes (Windows) or Finder (Mac).\n2. **Restore Backup:** Click on the device icon, then choose \"Restore Backup.\" Select the relevant backup to restore misc files.\n\n#### Apple Files App:\n1. **Open Files App:** Use the Files app to access various locations like iCloud Drive, Google Drive, Dropbox, etc.\n2. **Download Files:** Navigate to the specific folder containing your files and download them.\n\n### General Tips:\n- **Cloud Services:** Utilize cloud storage services like Google Drive, Dropbox, OneDrive to keep backups of miscellaneous files.\n- **File Management Apps:** Use specific file management apps like ES File Explorer (Android) or Documents by Readdle (iOS) to manage and restore files effectively.\n\nIt's crucial to consistently back up your data to avoid loss and ensure that you can restore files whenever necessary.",
